<HEADLINE> Arafat in Cairo for Talks on Mideast Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of the Palestinian
National Authority Yasser Arafat arrived in Cairo Tuesday evening
for a short visit after a trip to North African countries,
including Libya, Tunisia and Morocco.
</P>
<P>
President Hosni Mubarak will meet with Arafat Wednesday morning
to discuss the latest developments in the Middle East peace
process, Egyptian Foregin Minister Amr Moussa told reporters
earlier in the day.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak and Arafat will deal with the outcome of Arafat's
recent world tour, which is aimed at rallying support for his plan
to declare an independent Palestinian state, Moussa said.
</P>
<P>
Arafat has announced that he would declare Palestinian
statehood on May 4 when the five-year Palestinian interim autonomy
under the 1993 Oslo Accord signed with Israel expires.
</P>
<P>
He has been consulting with world leaders in recent weeks on
the Palestinian plan and trying to win their support for the step
and recognition for the future Palestinian state.
</P>
<P>
Arafat frequently visits Egypt to consult and coordinate
stances with Mubarak on the Mideast peace process, which has been
in a stalemate pending Israel's elections on May 17. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
