<HEADLINE> Russia Must Help Yugoslavia in Military, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Leader of the Russian Communist
Party Gennadii Zyuganov said here Tuesday that Russia must help
Yugoslavia in both military and humanitarian fields.
</P>
<P>
Zyuganov arrived here earlier Tuesday for a meeting of European
left-wing parties organized by Cyprus' Progressive Party of
Working People (AKEL) on the situation in Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Zyuganov underlined the need for a peaceful settlement to the
Yugoslav crisis considering the possibility that it may prompt
devastating consequences.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the need for cooperation among the left-wing
parties on the issue.
</P>
<P>
Zyuganov expressed concern that "NATO (the North Atlantic
Treaty Organization) and the United States have undertaken the
role of international caretakers," noting that this is detrimental
to Europe, which is going through a very crucial period.
</P>
<P>
Zyuganov said NATO is preparing to launch a ground campaign in
Yugoslavia and warned that "if they do so then there will be a new
Vietnam."
</P>
<P>
NATO started its massive air strikes against Yugoslavia on
March 24 allegely to punish Belgrade's refusal to sign a
Western-brokered peace deal with independence-seeking Kosovo
Albanians.
</P>
<P>
Leftist parties from Germany, Italy and Greece will also
participate in the two-day meeting to be held on April 21-22.
</P>
</TEXT>
