<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Expands Social Sector Quality Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian quality and
standards authority announced Tuesday that it is preparing to
expand its quality control to the social sector.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian News Agency, general manager of the
authority Mesay Girma told local press that the authority would
control the quality on, among others, health and educational
services.
</P>
<P>
The quality control service of the authority has so far been
restricted to the economic sector.
</P>
<P>
Mesay said the authority is at present boosting its manpower
and purchasing test equipment with the aim to launch its new
scheme.
</P>
<P>
He added that the authority has recently established 389
quality control categories and will soon add 228 others.  
