in two hours, 38 minutes over Henman.
</P>
<P>
Henman, the top British player and the No. 3 seed, missed his
big opportunity when he was leading 5-4 in the final set, reports
said.
</P>
<P>
A day after his victory over French No. 1 Cedric Pioline, Boris
Becker withdrew from the event after the death of his father, Karl-
Heinz, from stomach cancer.
</P>
