victory.
</P>
<P>
Key Biscayne finalist Sebastien Grosjean advanced to the second
round with a convincing 6-4, 6-0 win against Argentine qualifier
Sebastian Prieto.
</P>
<P>
The Frenchman will play No. 14 seed Tommy Haas in one of the
highlights of the second round.
</P>
<P>
Paraguay's Ramon Delgado, who beat Pete Sampras at last year's
French Open, defeated experienced Swede Jonas Bjorkman, 7-6 (7-5),
0-6, 6-4, to set up a second-round contest with No. 5 seed Mark
Philippoussis.
</P>
<P>
No. 10 seed Albert Costa and No. 12 seed Thomas Enqvist beat
Mariano Zabaleta and Dominik Hrbaty respectively, moving into the
second round. 
</P>
