<HEADLINE> Africa Ranks First in Refugee Origin Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Africa, which takes six of
the 10 major refugee countries of origin in the world, tops the
number of refugee origin countries in the world, according to the
U.N. High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR).
</P>
<P>
The top six African refugee countries of origin are: Sierra
Leone 440, 000, Somalia 419,000, Sudan 374,000, Eritrea 320,000,
Burundi 300,000 and Angola 255,000.
</P>
<P>
UNHCR said, the top four refugee hosting countries in Africa
are Guinea 470, 000, Sudan 390,000, Tanzania 330,000 and Ethiopia
317,000.
</P>
<P>
However, the top two refugee hosting countries worldwide are
Iran 1,980, 000 and Pakistan 1,200,000.
</P>
<P>
There were 7.2 million people covered by UNHCR in Africa, out
of an estimated 22.3 million worldwide, as of January 1998, UNHCR
said.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics provided recently by the UNHCR, the
Africa figure includes 3.5 million refugees, 1.5 million
internally displaced and 2.2 million former refugees who have
recently returned home.
</P>
<P>
While in January 1997, the global number of people of covered
by UNHCR was 22.7 million, of whom 8 million were in Africa,
according to UNHCR.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990421.0029 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Urges Social Funds to Be Developmental </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Social funds, often taken as
emergency funds, will yield better results if they are used by
development organizations with long term objectives, a World Bank
representative said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Azedine Ouerghi of the World Bank told participants to the
four-day African Social Investment Funds Network seminar in Harare
that social funds were perceived in some circles as responding to
crisis situations only.
</P>
<P>
"The effectiveness of social funds is realized by ability to
motivate developing social infrastructure and giving support to
the private sector," he said, adding that a long term objective
had to be in place.
</P>
<P>
He noted that recommendations were made at the International
Conference of Social Funds held in Washington two years ago.
</P>
<P>
They included the need to seek integration of social
development within the national macro-economic policies and
strategies for the reduction of poverty.
</P>
<P>
It was important for social funds, he said, to systematically
measure their innovations, capacity building and techniques
throughout the public sector.
</P>
<P>
Participants of this meeting were from Lesotho, Zimbabwe,
Zambia, Malawi and some European countries.
</P>
<P>
The seminar aims to bring together stakeholders in Social
Investment Funds to discuss how Social Funds can be used
productively for poverty alleviation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
