<HEADLINE> Italian FM: U.S. Cannot Be World's Policeman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The United States cannot be the
world's policeman nor can they serve as mercenaries for nations
which refuse to assume their military responsibilities, Italian
Foreign Minister Lamberto Dini said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Before being present at the joint meeting of the Lower House
foreign affairs and defense committees, Dini said that the
European Union had to "give itself a political personality for the
areas where it is most lacking: diplomacy and defense."
</P>
<P>
