Kosovo "has all at once shown how fragile a house which is just
built on the economy and a united currency, and never more than
today has there been a need for a united Europe."
</P>
<P>
Dini explained that in the Kosovo crisis Italy had always "done
its duty and fulfilled its commitments to the Alliance, but this
does not mean Italy can ignore the voices of its conscience and
reason." 
