<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-20 20:26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arab League Keen on Sustaining Human Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Arab League Secretary General Esmat
Abdel-Meguid said Tuesday that the pan-Arab organization is keen
on sustaining the human development effort it started nearly two
decades ago.
</P>
<P>
Abdel-Meguid made the remark in a speech to the 15th Arab
annual conference opened here Tuesday on the development of human
resources. Daw Sweidan, Abdel-Meguid's assistant, read the speech
on his behalf.
</P>
<P>
The league chief underlined the importance of providing Arabs
with quality education and good health in an effort to help
promote the human development drive.
</P>
<P>
In 1980, the Arab countries endorsed a strategy for joint Arab
economic action and attached special importance to the problem of
Arab housing as a pillar of the human development process.
</P>
<P>
The three-day conference, held under the auspices of the Arab
League in cooperation with Egypt's Ministry of Higher Education,
will seek solution to the problems facing the development of human
resources in the Arab countries, Egypt's Middle East News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
It will discuss the non-governmental organizations' role in
enhancing the human development process and the strategy that they
could come up with in this respect.
</P>
<P>
It will probe the possibility that international and regional
funding institutions may play a role in boosting human development
activities, with an emphasis on the private sector and
businessmen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
