<HEADLINE> Experts to Look into Health, Environment in New Century </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Dozens of international
experts are expected to attend a conference on health and
environment at the United Nations headquarters this week to deal
with a number of issues of significance in the next century.
</P>
<P>
Announcing this on Tuesday, the U.N. said the meeting will
focus on the environmental trends adversely affecting human health
in the new millennium and on the specific impact of environmental
degradation on different age groups especially older persons and
youth.
</P>
<P>
The subjects include health in developing countries in the 21st
century, environmental factors affecting the health of workers,
the genetic effects of nuclear fallout, melanoma and climate
change, tourism and sexually transmitted diseases.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. Department of Public Information said the two-day
meeting from Thursday to Friday was organized by a
non-governmental organization called World Information Transfer
(WIT). It is expected to be attended by physicians, scientists and
diplomatic experts from around the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
