<HEADLINE> Wang Zhizhi and Bater Head China's New Men's Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- China Wednesday announced its
men's national training team for participating in the Asian
Basketball Championship which starting in late August in Fukuoda,
Japan, with Wang Zhizhi of the Bayi Rockets and Bater of the
Beijing Ducks among the roster.
</P>
<P>
Wang is leading the defending champion on the way to their
fifth straight title of the CBA new league with a 2-0 lead in the
best-of-five finals, while Bater is just back from a NBA team of
the Sun's training camp on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Wang Fei, head coach of the Rockets, will guard the 15-member
training team, which will begin the training on May 15 in Beijing.
Zhang Bin, former head coach of the Jinan Army, was named as
Wang's assistant.
</P>
<P>
Wang teamed Zhang led China to won back the Asian men's
basketball crown from arch-rival South Korea at the Bangkok Asian
Games in December last year.
</P>
<P>
Following are the roster of the Chinese national training squad,
released by the Chinese Basketball Association:
</P>
<P>
Guards: Li Xiaoyong of the Liaoning Hunters, Fan Bin of the
Rockets, Li Qun of the Guangdong Tigers;
</P>
<P>
Centers: Wang Zhizhi, Bater, Yao MIng of the Shanghai Sharks;
</P>
<P>
Forwards: Sun Jun of Liaoning Tigers, Zhang Wenqi of Shanghai
Sharks, Hu Weidong and Zhang Cheng of the Jiangsu Dragons, Gong
Xiaobin and Cheng Zhiming of the Shandong Flaming Bulls, Liu
Yudong, Zhang Jiangsong and Li Nan of the Rockets.
</P>
<P>
The Men's Asian Basketball Championship, also serves as the
quarlifier for the 2000 Sydney Olympic Games, will be held on
August 28 through September 5 in Japan, where only one team win
the right to represent Asia for the Olympics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
