<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Vice-Premier Emphasizes Prevention Of Epidemics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Vice-premier Li Lanqing said
today that northeast China should pay more attention to preventing
epidemics during a period of time when serious epidemic diseases
could break out.
</P>
<P>
He asked local governments to take steps to prevent the spread
of serious epidemic diseases and said that things should not be
left up to chance.
</P>
<P>
So far, no serious epidemic diseases have broken out in Jilin
or Heilongjiang provinces or in the Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region, the sites of last year's serious flooding and infectious
diseases have been brought under control.
</P>
<P>
However, the incidence of certain infectious diseases like
dysentery is climbing and there could be breakouts of some
diseases, doctors warn.
</P>
<P>
The prevention tasks are still serious and the many dead animal
carcasses that froze last year are a big health threat, he said,
asking local governments to take steps as soon as possible to deal
with these carcasses.
</P>
<P>
Li warned that regional officials in charge of the work will be
dealt with seriously if big problems occur and he asked local
departments to cooperate in helping flood victims.
</P>
<P>
He also mentioned the necessity of establishing an emergency
medical group and improving public awareness of medicines.
</P>
</TEXT>
