<HEADLINE> China Improving Safety On Major Highways </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- China's Public Security Ministry
wants to improve safety of two major highways between Beijing and
the cities of Harbin and Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has asked the local governments along the two
highways to keep overloaded and unlicensed vehicles off the
highways before October 1 this year, which is the 50th anniversary
of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has also asked local departments to prevent
serious accidents and to continue the crackdown on criminal
activities along the highways.
</P>
<P>
Local police need greater discipline and should not encroach on
local people's interests, the ministry says. It has asked local
departments to accept criticism from the public and to improve
their work. 
</P>
