<HEADLINE> Beijing's First Sub-Health Outpatient Service For Certain Diseases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Donghua Hospital in Beijing's
Chongwen District opened its first outpatient service for certain
medical problems today because of greater attention from doctors
and society, hospital sources say.
</P>
<P>
It deals with more than 100 problems from depression and
anxiety to diseases of the tongue, skin, and internal organs.
</P>
<P>
Some analysts blame the growing incidence of certain health
problems on physical and mental fatigue caused by overwork, the
aging process, trauma from childbirth and surgery, and periodic
depression.
</P>
<P>
Doctors at the hospital have tried to find better ways to deal
with these conditions by using traditional Chinese medicines and
therapy and have treated more than 1,000 patients in this way at
the hospital. 
