<HEADLINE> Bank Of China Becomes Custodian Of New Investment Fund </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China (BOC) and
Dacheng Fund Management Co. Ltd. signed an agreement here today
making the BOC custodian of the Jinghong Securities Investment
Fund, the first investment fund to have such an arrangement with
the BOC.
</P>
<P>
The fund will be issued on April 27 with a total face value of
2 billion yuan, jointly sponsored by Everbright Securities Co. Ltd.
, Dapeng Securities Co. Ltd., the China Economic Development Trust
Investment Co., Guangdong Securities Co. Ltd., and Dacheng.
</P>
<P>
A BOC spokesman said that, as the nominal holder of Jinghong,
the bank will do its best to take care of the fund's assets and
supervise managerial operations. It will also closely cooperate
with Dacheng to protect investors' rights and interests.
</P>
<P>
He said that since BOC's fund trust division was set up at the
end of 1998, it has designed strict internal control systems, risk-
prevention systems, and operational procedures and has established
offices in Shanghai and Shenzhen, China's two securities trading
centers.
</P>
<P>
BOC's vice-president, Zhao Ange, said that his bank will make
full use of its domestic and overseas business advantages to get
involved in the open-ended trust business as soon as possible.
</P>
