<HEADLINE> Luxembourg Providing Medical Assistance To Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The government of Luxembourg
donated 730,000 U.S. dollars today for medical projects in China's
Tibet Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The money will be used to purchase medical equipment and to
train professionals to improve safety and disease prevention in
the region.
</P>
<P>
According to local medical officials, Tibet's medical
facilities are not sufficient to deal with the 50,000 newly-born
babies every year. They say that with the help of foreign
countries and international organizations and the efforts of local
officials, many diseases are under control in the region.
</P>
<P>
The life expectancy of Tibetans has increased from 36 years in
1952 to 66 years today, and Tibet's population has grown from 1.15
million in 1952 to 2.5 million. 
