<HEADLINE> 35th Plenary Session of Sino-Portuguese JLG Closes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The two-day 35th plenary session
of the Sion-Portuguese Joint Liaison Group (JLG), discussing the
transfer of power and other major transition issues in Macao,
closed here today.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Han Zhaokang, chief Chinese representative, said at
a press conference today that China is closely concerned with the
pressing issues such as the ceremony of transfer of power and the
arrangement of stationing troops in Macao.
</P>
<P>
He said that during the meeting the two sides discussed issues
including localization of senior civil servants and laws, the
official status of Chinese language, pensions of public
functionaries, Macao's participation in international
organizations and the concrete arrangement of the transfer of
power and station of troops.
</P>
<P>
Portuguese chief representative Ambassador Antonio Santana
Carlos said the session is satisfactory and the two sides had
taken an active attitude in dealing with the issues.
</P>
<P>
The two sides have reached common understanding and signed
minutes of talks during the meeting on the contract of exclusive
operation of the Macao Power Company.
</P>
<P>
The issues of common understanding also include Macao's
participation in International Labor Organization and Hague
Conference on Private International Law after December 20, 1999,
direction policies on the transfer of Macao documents, and issue
of stamps featuring the transition of Macao.
</P>
<P>
According to Han Zhaokang, the JLG will hold unofficial talks
in Xi'an, capital of northwest China's Shaanxi Province during
April 22-23. 
</P>
</TEXT>
