<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rebound on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Share prices bounced back
Wednesday after Tuesday's sharp fall on the Singapore Stock Market
amid active buying in blue chips and higher retail interest in
second liners following a slight overnight recovery on Wall Street
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index closed up 32.85 points and
ended at 1842.33 points, rebounding to the level of a 18-month
close high.
</P>
