cents to close at 15.00 Singapore dollars. DBS F and SPH 100
retreated 30 cents to finish at 16.50 and 24.50 Singapore dollars
respectively. CMSPort dropped 13.5 cents to end at 1.99 Singapore
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said technical rebound after yesterday's losses and the
picking up of laggard small cap stocks by retail investors
contributed to Wednesday's strong rally.
</P>
<P>
In morning dealings, institutional investors were switching to
laggard blue chips as well, they added. 
