<HEADLINE> Yunnan Reports Rising First Quarter Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Yunnan Province
reported an import-export volume of 371 million U.S. dollars for
the first quarter of the year, up 13.2 percent on the same period
last year.
</P>
<P>
Statistics for the first three months show that Yunnan exported
a total of 226 million dollars of goods, up 5.8 percent on the
previous year.
</P>
<P>
Marked growth was reported for main exports such as chemicals,
mining products and nonferrous metals, as well as electronic,
pharmaceutical and agricultural products.
</P>
<P>
The province's import volume jumped 27 percent to 145 million
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The forthcoming World Horticulture Expo scheduled for Kunming
has sparked a construction boom and increased the demands for
imported raw materials, equipment and machinery, according to
local officials.
</P>
<P>
The Asian financial crisis which erupted in 1997 has adversely
impacted the province's foreign trade sector which focuses on
Southeast Asian markets.
</P>
<P>
However, the province reversed the declining trend last year
and reported a 1.1 percent rise which ended the period at 2.03
billion dollars.  
</P>
