<HEADLINE> More Laws For Southern Chinese City This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The southern Chinese coastal
city of Shenzhen plans to draw up 37 laws or regulations this year
to create a better judicial environment, officials said here today.
</P>
<P>
The legislative plan was approved by the municipal government
today and will focus on improving the municipal management and
building a social security system.
</P>
<P>
