<HEADLINE> Singapore Deputy Prime Minister Urges for Strong Euro-Asia Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SINGAPORE, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Deputy Prime Minister
Lee Hsien Loong has urged for a strong ties between Europe and
Asia for the benefits of both regions, Television Corporation of
Singapore broadcast Wednesday in a report from Germany.
</P>
<P>
Lee made the point in his speech delivered to a forum in
Hamburg, Germany, while on a two-week European tour which has
taken him to the United Kingdom, Ireland, France and Germany.
</P>
<P>
Lee said Asia and Europe should not let their strategic
relationship become more distant as strong ties between Asia and
Europe remained vital to both regions.
</P>
<P>
For Asia, Lee underlined, Europe is both a key support market
and a source of capital and technology.
</P>
<P>
While for Europe, he said, Asia rivals the United States in
terms of market size, adding in 1997 Asia overtook the United
States as Europe's largest trading partner.
</P>
<P>
He drew attention to the fact that Euro-Asia trade accounted for
some three million jobs in Europe and held that an economic
recovery in Asia would contribute significantly to Europe's
prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Conversely, Lee said, Asia needed a strong Europe to ensure a
global environment that is conducive to recovery.
</P>
<P>
Noting that both Asia and Europe have been pre-occupied with
developments in their own regions over the last two years with
Asian countries focusing on fixing their economies while European
countries adapting to the launch of the single European currency
plus the crisis in Kosovo, he urged European companies to take a
long-term view over Asia and help Asia out of crisis through
investment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
