that the only solution to the Kosovo problem lies in peace talks.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with a delegation of Greek parliamentarians led by
Karolos Papoulias, the chairman of the Foreign Affairs and Defense
Committee of the Greek Parliament, Li reiterated China's stance on
the Kosovo issue, which calls for an immediate halt to the NATO
bombing on Yugoslavia and the instant resumption of peace talks.
</P>
<P>
Papoulias said that Greece appreciates China's position on the
Kosovo issue and is worried about the expansion and escalation of
the NATO bombing and that the pressure Greece feels from the
Kosovo refugee issue is increasing.
</P>
<P>
He said Greece hopes that the parties concerned can settle the
issue through peaceful means.
</P>
<P>
Li said that during his visit to Greece earlier this month, he
and Greek leaders discussed the Kosovo issue and found that they
have identical views.
</P>
<P>
Papoulias told Li that Greece places emphasis on China's role
in international affairs and on increasing Sino-Greek relations.
</P>
<P>
Li said he hopes that exchanges and cooperation between the
parliaments of the two countries will be strengthened and
Papoulias said that his committee will continue to work for the
development of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
The Greek delegation members are here as guests of the Chinese
People's Foreign Affairs Institute. 
