<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Weaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar ended
softer Wednesday but off its session lows as the unit found
support from participants.
</P>
<P>
Traders said there was two way action in the market, with
buyers happy to prop up the currency whenever it appeared to slip.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar closed in Sydney at 64.88 U.S. cents from
Tuesday's finish of 65.03 U.S. cents.
</P>
<P>
During local dealings Wednesday it hit a high of 64.95 U.S.
cents and marked a low of 64.59 U.S. cents.
</P>
<P>
According to Arab Bank's Scott Young, overseas interest in the
Australian dollar will continue as reports confirm that Asia is
beginning to emerge from its financial crisis, while market
perceptions about the safety of the local currency will continue
to lure more buyers.
</P>
<P>
At the close in Sydney, the Australian dollar was buying 0.6109
euro from 0.60101 euro and 76.96 Japanese yen from 76.79 yen at
Tuesday's close, while the euro was trading at 1.0627 U.S. dollars
from 1.0660 U.S. dollars. 
</P>
