</P>
<P>
The benchmark all ordinaries index shed 21.8 points to close at
3068.3, following on from a 23 point slide on Tuesday which ended
a five-day record breaking rising streak on the market.
</P>
<P>
Reynolds &AMP; Co adviser Peter Struk said the local bourse was a
little nervous that United States markets could deteriorate.
</P>
<P>
