<HEADLINE> Dhaka Hosts Meeting on World Conference on Science </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- A one-day meeting of the Center for
Science and Technology of the Non-Aligned and Other Development
Countries was held here on Wednesday to seek a common stand for
the coming World Conference on Science scheduled for later this
year.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from Bangladesh, India, Nepal, Pakistan,
Indonesia, Malaysia, Sri Lanka and Zambia presented their
respective views on economic globalization, the free flow of
information, and other issues concerning the world science
conference.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, however, failed to adopt a Dhaka communique, as
most of the participants said they were not "in a position to make
a country stance" on the issue.
</P>
<P>
The statement would be announced in one or two weeks' time
after all participating countries made their responses to the
draft communique, M. Fazlur Rahman, secretary of the Ministry of
Science and Technology, told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was jointly sponsored by the Center for Science and
Technology of the Non-aligned and Other Developing Countries, and
the Ministry of Science and Technology of Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
The second World Conference on Science will be held in
Budapest, Hungary, from June 26 to July 1 this year. 
</P>
