<HEADLINE> China Launches Charity Drive for Cancer Patients </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- China's major charity
organization plans to launch a national rehabilitation and fund-
raising campaign to help cancer patients.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the campaign, sponsored by the China Charity
Federation (CCF), is to provide financial aid to poor patients and
fund the establishment of a national center for cancer
rehabilitation.
</P>
<P>
Cancer, which hits some 1.6 million Chinese people and claims 1.
3 million lives each year, ranks as the No.1 cause of death among
urban Chinese and the third greatest health problem in rural areas.
The incidence rate for cancers continues to rise due to aging
population, industrialization and high-risk lifestyles, according
to the Anti-Cancer Association of China which is participating in
the project.
</P>
<P>
The high mortality rate for the disease and high cost of
medical care leave most patients with feelings of depression,
helplessness and desperation.
</P>
<P>
One cancer rehabilitation expert that cancer patients should
have access to surgery, radiotherapy and chemotherapy, as well as
comprehensive treatment which focuses on psychological counseling,
nutrition, exercise and healthy lifestyles.
</P>
<P>
"However, China's rehabilitation services fail to meet current
demand in spite of rehabilitation organizations established in 50-
plus cities," according to Zhang Zongwei with the Beijing Tumor
Hospital.
</P>
<P>
The charity campaign will enable experts to seek better
rehabilitation methods with Chinese characteristics, including the
introduction of traditional herbal medicine and qigong, a system
featuring deep breathing exercises, said Zhang. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
