<HEADLINE> Another Bomb Threat Shocks Capital Of Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Bomb threat once again shocked
the capital of Indonesia when security guard found a black leather
briefcase in front of Bank RAMA at Jalan Thamrin, Central Jakarta,
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
It was 11:45 a.m. when some workers that were out for lunch
called security guard to inform about a briefcase placed under a
crossing bridge in front of the bank.
</P>
<P>
The Special Bomb Squad later arrived at 14:45, secured the area
and took a X-ray photo. The suspected briefcase was then
transferred to the Second Police Regiment's Headquarters.
</P>
<P>
Although the head of the Special Bomb Squad refuse to confirm
the bomb inside the briefcase before further investigations, he
did say that judging from the X-ray photo, there was strong
indication that it was a bomb.
</P>
<P>
This was the third bomb that shocked Jakarta in just seven
days. The first exploded last Thursday damaging a store with no
casualties, and the second one last Monday injured 5 persons at
the basement office of Istiqlal Mosque. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
