<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Exports, Imports Soar in First Two Months of 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Both imports into and exports from
Macao increased substantially in the first two months of this year,
according to figures released Wednesday by the Macao Census and
Statistics Department.
</P>
<P>
Exports in January and February were 2.487 billion patacas (
about 310.9 million U.S. dollars), up 22.5 percent from the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
Imports during that period reached 2.424 billion patacas (303
million U.S. dollars), an increase of 23.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Due to more imports, however, the trade surplus of 63 million
patacas (7.875 million U.S. dollars) in the period decreased 14.1
percent compared with the same period of 1998.
</P>
<P>
Particularly in February, exports and imports surged 45.5
percent and 35.3 percent respectively over the second month of
last year.
</P>
<P>
Textiles and garments remained the leading export items of
Macao, accounting for 83 percent of all exports.
</P>
<P>
The statistics also show that 78.8 percent of Macao's exports
were shipped to the United States and the European Union.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, most of the imports came from the Asian Pacific
region, including China's mainland and Hong Kong, which supplied
42 percent of imported goods. 
</P>
</TEXT>
