<DOCNO> XIE19990421.0146 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rwandan Govt Urged to Take Y2K Problem Seriously </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The Rwandan government has been
advised to be more serious about the Year 2000 millenium problem.
</P>
<P>
Augustine Bushayija, coordinator of the Y2K millenium problem,
told Rwanda News Agency (RNA) that the Rwandan government is not
taking the problem seriously compared to Uganda, Kenya and
Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
"The Rwandan government set aside a very small percentage of
the budget for the Y2K problem, yet Rwanda has to employ
expatriates since there are few local qualified personnel,"
Bushayija highlighted.
</P>
<P>
"Top government officials are not actively involved in the Y2K
committee as in other countries", he added.
</P>
<P>
The Rwandan government paid only 25 percent of money requested
for secretarial services.
</P>
<P>
There remained only 226 days, last Friday when they held their
two-day seminar but, top government lawmakers did not turn up, he
said.
</P>
<P>
"I call upon the Rwandan government, to inject in more
resources even though it is very expensive, as 1st January 2000 is
drawing nearer," Bushayija indicated.
</P>
<P>
According to Gerald Mpyisi, the coordinator of the Y2K
Millenium bug in Rwanda, crucial departments will be affected if
they are not Y2K compliant. These include air transport,
ELECTROGAZ, Rwandatel, Hospitals, Insurances, ministries,
government account department pay rolls, banking and finance.
</P>
<P>
If by 2000 such important departments are not Y2K compliant, it
will have negative economic impacts to the Rwandan government;
national business and computerized services will all be affected,
Mpyisi underscored.
</P>
<P>
Samson Goloba Y2K Millenium officer in Rwanda told Rwanda News
Agency that reports from Washington revealed that, in July 1998,
IBM Computer Manufacturing Company in USA Manufactured 60 percent
Y2K compliant and 40 percent non compliant computers.
</P>
<P>
He advised Rwandans to purchase Y2K compliant computers to curb
the prevailing problem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
