<HEADLINE> Chain Stores Enjoy Rising First Quarter Sales </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- China's chain stores continued to
enjoy rising sales in the first quarter of the year, with total
sales up 26.9 percent on last year's same period, according to a
report by the State Administration of Internal Trade.
</P>
<P>
The total retail sales volume of chain stores nationwide hit 4.
98 billion yuan (about 60 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
China has 1,441 chain stores, 313 stores more than in the first
quarter of last year, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
The number of supermarkets surged by 55.8 percent, with the
number of large warehouse stores growing by 33.3 percent and the
number of convenience stores remaining unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Supermarket retail sales grew by 34.4 percent, with the figure
for large warehouse stores up 15.7 percent and convenience stores
by 10.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Products with the largest sales volumes included frozen foods,
snacks, tonics, wine and cooked meat.
</P>
<P>
The sales volume of China's chain stores hit 100 billion yuan
last year, up almost 70 percent on the previous year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
