<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Jobs Created in Philippines January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Despite the Asian financial
upheaval, about 679,000 additional workers were employed in
January 1999 in the Philippines, a government news release said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The number of employed persons rose to 28.37 million in January
from 27.69 million in the same month of 1998, representing a
year-on-year increase of 2.4 percent or of 679,000 jobs, the news
release said.
</P>
<P>
The growth rate could be attributed to improvements in the
agricultural and financial sectors, which were badly hit by the
prolonged drought and the Asian financial crisis, it said.
</P>
<P>
The agricultural, fishery and forestry sector is leading the
employment growth as more Filipino workers found jobs in 1999 than
in 1998, it added.
</P>
<P>
Following the agricultural and financial fields are the
transportation and communications sector, which offered 5.8
percent more jobs in January, the news release said.
</P>
<P>
The largest employment increment was recorded in metro Manila,
which had some 134,000 new jobs, it said.
</P>
<P>
Metro Manila was followed by southern Luzon with 89,000 new
jobs and central Luzon with 88,000, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
