<HEADLINE> UNHCR Regrets NATO Refusal to Share Information on Kosovo Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations High
Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) Sadako Ogata has expressed her
regret that NATO refuses to share information on the exodus of
Kosovo refugees.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the French daily Liberation published on
Wednesday, Ogata said that the UNHCR is having a complicated
relationship with NATO, which is running refugee camps in Albania
and Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
"I asked NATO to share information on the displaced people
which it has received due to air reconnaissance, but up to now, it
has refused to do so," said Ogata.
</P>
<P>
She said that the UNHCR does not have the capacity to lead the
humanitarian operation for hundreds of thousands of Kosovo
refugees, unless NATO countries provide "an extra contribution."
</P>
<P>
"Nobody, I say nobody, has ever foreseen that expulsions of
such a massive scale could take place. I have never found a person
who could have imagined such a catastrophe," she said.
</P>
<P>
She expected that the number of refugees from Kosovo will soon
attain 900,000. 
</P>
