<HEADLINE> Macao Housing Deals Remain Sluggish in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 21 (Xinhua) -- A total of 87 buildings were
completed in Macao in 1998, 21 fewer than in 1997, latest figures
from the Macao Census and Statistics Department show.
</P>
<P>
Among the buildings, 59.8 percent are residential apartments
and the rest are to be used as offices, stores and workshops.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, 12,776 housing units were sold, 59.1 percent of which
were in newly-constructed buildings and 40.9 percent in old
buildings. The number of transactions dropped 10.7 percent from
that in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Macao has been suffering from an economic slowdown since the
mid-1990s due to the adverse economic circumstances in the
surrounding areas and a bad economic structure in Macao.
</P>
<P>
Many people predict that the upcoming handover will boost the
local economy and that the first chief executive of the future
Macao Special Administrative Region will be able to help usher in
a period of prosperity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
