<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africa to Build Houses for 400,000 People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 21 (Xinhua) -- South Africa will build
houses for 400,000 people in Gauteng, a province where cities of
Johannesburg and Pretoria are situated, a senior official has
said.
</P>
<P>
A total of 176,240 housing units, to be built mostly by black
developers, would be erected across the entire province, Dan
Mofokeng, top official responsible for housing and land affairs in
the province, said Tuesday at the signing of a public declaration.
</P>
<P>
The development project will cost 960 million rand or 160
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Gauteng Province led the country by building 103,700 housing
units, which had already benefited about 400,000 people by March
this year.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the provincial government has provided about
80,000 people with water and sanitation over the past five years,
Mofeng said.
</P>
<P>
Gauteng is the smallest but the most densely populated province
in South Africa. It was estimated that about 40,000 people,
mostly blacks, flood into the region per month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
