<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hangzhou-Xiaoshan Airport Under Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Full-scale construction of
Hangzhou-Xiaoshan International Airport in east China's Zhejiang
Province commenced today.
</P>
<P>
The 484-ha airport, located 27 km east of downtown Hangzhou,
the provincial capital, will be constructed in three phases. It is
designed to handle eight million passengers and 75,000 tons of
cargo annually.
</P>
<P>
First phase construction will be completed by the end of next
year at a cost of 2.77 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The airport complex will include a 3,600-m runway, terminal
building covering 70,000 sq.m. and 12 parking aprons, as well as
navigation, telecommunications and lighting systems. It is capable
of accommodating large airplane such as Boeing 747-400.
</P>
<P>
Hangzhou, one of China's most popular tourism cities, currently
has one airport serving both civilian and military aircraft.
</P>
<P>
The decision to build the new airport was announced in 1992.
</P>
</TEXT>
