<HEADLINE> CPC Values Ties With African National Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Vice-President Hu Jintao said
here today in a meeting with a delegation of South Africa's
African National Congress led by its National Chairman Patrick
Lekota that the Communist Party of China values its relationship
with the ANC.
</P>
<P>
To further consolidate their friendship and to increase
exchanges on building the party and the country will benefit
relations between the two countries. As the ruling parties in the
two countries, the CPC and ANC both have the great task of
developing the economy, improving the standard of living, and
safeguarding world peace and stability, Hu said.
</P>
<P>
China and South Africa have a sound traditional friendship and,
especially since the diplomatic relations were established in 1998,
bilateral ties have entered into a new development era, he said.
High level exchanges of visits have increased as has cooperation
in various sectors, producing good results, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said that strengthening friendly cooperation with developing
countries in Africa and elsewhere has always been a major part of
China's independent foreign policy of peace and that China is
willing to expand cooperation with African nations in various
fields and jointly bring long-term, stable and vigorous relations
to the next century.
</P>
<P>
Lekota said that South Africa will never forget China's support
for its struggle for democracy, freedom, and national liberation,
and the ANC is playing an important role in realizing national
reconciliation, maintaining social stability, developing the
economy, and promoting peace in Africa and ANC hopes to continue
to develop relations with the CPC to jointly push bilateral ties
forward.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is in China at the invitation of the CPC.
