<HEADLINE> ICBC Pledges Strengthened Support for Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The Industrial and Commercial
Bank of China (ICBC), one of the country's four state banks, today
pledged to improve financial services for small- and medium-sized
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The ICBC plans to offer various financial services, including
settlements and remittances, according to bank officials.
</P>
<P>
The bank will also simplify procedures for granting credit
lines to promote the development of related enterprises, in
addition to providing information services and financial
consulting.
</P>
<P>
Profitable companies and ventures in promising industries will
be granted priority for related services.
</P>
<P>
China's 10 million small- to medium-sized enterprises account
for 90 percent of the nation's total number of registered
enterprises and generate some 60 percent of the gross industrial
output value and 40 percent of total profits and taxes.
</P>
<P>
The government attaches great importance to the development of
such enterprises and has introduced a series of favorable policies
to promote the sector's growth. 
</P>
