<HEADLINE> 15 Tamil Rebels Killed in Sri Lankan Fighting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
Tuesday killed 15 Tamil rebels in separate clashes with guerrillas
of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) in the north of the
country, the Defense Ministry said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The troops engaged a group of rebels with small arms and
machine arms in Jaffna and killed seven rebels, the ministry said
in a press release.
</P>
<P>
In Andankulam, troops located a rebel hideout and destroyed it
with small arms and rocket-propelled grenade fire, killing six
rebels.
</P>
<P>
Another two rebels were killed in two separate clashes in the
north of Mankulam and Oddusudan, all in the Wanni area.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a separatist war against the Sri
Lankan government since 1983 for an independent Tamil homeland in
the north and east of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
