<HEADLINE> ROK Cargo Plane Crash Not Caused By Explosives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- A team of investigators from
China, the Republic of Korea (ROK), and the United States has
ruled out the possibility that the ROK cargo plane that crashed
last Thursday was brought down by explosives or inflammable items.
</P>
<P>
No evidence of explosives or a cargo overload has been found
and the cause of the crash, which killed eight people, including
three crew members, and left six people with serious injuries, is
still under investigation.
</P>
<P>
The MD-11 took off from Shanghai's Hongqiao Airport at 16:04 (
Beijing time) on Thursday for Seoul. It reached an altitude of 1,
000 meters before falling into a construction site in the city's
Minhang District, killing four construction workers instantly and
injuring 35 other people.
</P>
<P>
The cargo plane was reportedly carrying 68 tons of mushrooms,
some machine parts, and other items. 
</P>
</TEXT>
