<DOCNO> XIE19990421.0219 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rwanda Shuns Signing Congo (K) Peace Deal: Envoy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mwenze Kongolo, a special envoy sent by Congolese President
Laurent Kabila to Zimbabwe told the Zimbabwe News Agency in Harare
that Rwandan Vice President and strongman Kagame was invited to
Tripoli.
</P>
<P>
Kongolo briefed Robert Mugabe on the deal, saying that a
meeting was being organized for Lusaka, Zambia, where the deal
could be worked further by all countries involved in the conflict
in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC).
</P>
<P>
"There is also another meeting in Italy on April 30 where the
deal will be finalized," said Kongolo.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe's Foreign Minister Stan Mudenge said Zimbabwe had been
aware of the signing which took the whole world by surprise as its
preparations were secretive, true to Gaddafi's style of scheming.
</P>
<P>
"President Mugabe is very happy because this is what we have
always wanted. He emphasized that it will be appropriate to have
a summit before the deal can be implemented by officials," said
Mudenge.
</P>
<P>
Kognolo did not have information from the war front but he and
Mudenge agreed that nothing was expected to change until the deal
is implemented.
</P>
<P>
Kongolo was also scheduled to travel to Namibia and Zambia on
the same mission. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
