<DOCNO> XIE19990421.0233 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Most Ethiopia's State-owned Firms at Profit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Out of the 163 state-owned
development enterprises in Ethiopia, 114 are operating profitably,
according to Assefa Abraha, an official in charge of state-owned
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Assefa was quoted by Wednesday's Ethiopian Herald newspaper as
saying that the 114 enterprises made pre-tax profits totalling
about 227 million U. S. dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, the remaining 49 organizations, some of which
are textile factories, incurred a loss of nearly 34 million
dollars in the same period.
</P>
<P>
Major efforts have been underway to ensure that members of the
administrations assigned to these enterprises are drawn from
various professional fields, said the official, adding that a
total of 596 experts including legal, management and engineering
staff are needed for the job at the moment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
