<HEADLINE> Kenya's Exports to Egypt Top $100 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Kenya's exports of tea and coffee
to Egypt top 6.5 billion shillings (100 million U.S. dollars)
annually, a senior Kenyan official has revealed.
</P>
<P>
The Daily Nation newspaper Wednesday quoted Permanent Secretary
F. Awuor of Kenyan Trade Ministry as saying that trade between
the two countries was in favor of Kenya.
</P>
<P>
Awuor told a trade delegation from Egypt that Kenya played an
active role in Egypt's entry into the Common Market for Eastern
and Southern Africa (COMESA) recently.
</P>
<P>
Awuor urged Egyptian business community to identify investment
areas in Kenya or seek joint ventures with Kenyans now that Kenya
has liberalized and opened up its economy.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Ambassador to Kenya Mohammed Ibrahim said although
Egyptian exports to Kenya totalled only six million U.S. dollars,
the two countries should increase the trade volume rather than
correcting trade imbalances.
</P>
<P>
He said nowadays Egypt imports large quantity of tea from Kenya
and won't reduce the quantity just because Kenya imports less.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
