<DOCNO> XIE19990421.0249 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Wildlife Habitat Created in Northern Shaanxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Shaanxi Province
has turned the Huanglong Mountain Forest Zone into a new habitat
for wildlife, thanks to a series of protective measures instituted
in recent years.
</P>
<P>
According to a recent survey, the Huanglong Mountain Forest
Zone, located southeast of the Loess Plateau, is now the home of
122 wild animal species, including such rare breeds, all under top
state protection, as the leopard, red-crowned crane, and golden
eagle.
</P>
<P>
The leopard, which had disappeared from the region in 1997, has
recently returned to its original habitat, and the crossoptilon
mantchuricum, a rare type of chicken considered the fifth national
animal treasure in China after the giant panda, golden monkey,
ibis and takin, was found living in the region last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990421.0250 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading French newspapers on Wednesday:
</P>
