<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Court Begins Hearings on Gitic Liquidation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The court hearing in China's
first case of liquidation and bankruptcy for a financial
institution - the Guangdong International Trust and Investment
Corp.(Gitic)- began Tuesday in Shenzhen in south China's Guangdong
Province, bordering Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
A source with the Higher People's Court of Guangdong Province
said that the Shenzhen Intermediate Court, the Guangzhou
Intermediate Court and the Provincial Higher Court will convene a
series of separate creditors meetings through Thursday to deal
with the case.
</P>
<P>
It has been reported that Gitic's liquidation proceedings will
be handled in four parts, according to Gitic's assets which are
divided among its four companies: Gitic headquarters, Guangxing
Enterprise Co., Gitic Shenzhen Co. Ltd. and Guangdong
International Leasing Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The Provincial Higher Court formally agreed to proceed with
bankruptcy at the end of last year, making Gitic China's first
financial institution allowed to go bankrupt. This is the first
court hearing convened for Gitic's creditors.
</P>
<P>
The court has appointed a liquidation committee for the
creditors meetings, which is in line with international practices
protecting the creditors' interests by facilitating communication
between the court and the creditors.
</P>
<P>
At the meetings, a report will be presented on Gitic's
financial losses, total company assets, the committee's work on
debt repayment, and Gitic's overseas investments. The courts will
also discuss the disposal of the company's assets with the
creditors.
</P>
<P>
The chief judge has pledged to Gitic's creditors that the court
will make the maximum effort to protect their rights and deal with
the case according to law and international practices.
</P>
<P>
Gitic, the investment arm of booming Guangdong Province, was
closed by the People's Bank of China, the country's central bank,
in October 1998 because of its failure to repay outstanding debts.
Gitic has assets of 21.47 billion yuan, and debts amounting to 36.
15 billion yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
