<HEADLINE> North China Inspires Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, April 21 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei Province
has recently offered another 300 projects for foreign investment
as the province's Foreign Trade and Economic Fair from May 18 to
22 approaches.
</P>
<P>
The projects include many industries such as power,
transportation, electronics, machinery, chemicals, light
industrials, agriculture, animal husbandry, textiles, construction
materials, and environmental protection. The total investment
sought for these industries is 4 billion U.S. dollars, among which
2.1 billion is expected to come from foreign countries.
</P>
<P>
Song Xiaoying, vice director of the Hebei Economic and Trade
Commission, said the province will intensify its efforts to
utilize foreign investment in the technological upgrading of more
than 200 enterprises with a total investment of 1.2 billion U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The government also offered 14 property-right transfer projects
involving nine industries, including machinery, textiles, food,
and pharmaceuticals, seeking foreign capital of 130 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Hebei has established trade ties with over 100 countries and
regions, and used 2.01 billion U.S. dollars last year, including
foreign investment for technological upgrading projects totaling
640 million U.S. dollars, 20.4 percent more than in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The province, located east of the Bohai Sea, claims it has
convenient transportation, a broad market, an abundance of natural
resources, and a large labor force. 
</P>
</TEXT>
