<HEADLINE> Spurs Beat Jazz to Clinch Playoff Berth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Tim Duncan scored 23 of his 36
points in the second half to pace the San Antonio Spurs for an 83-
69 victory over the Utah Jazz on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Duncan also grabbed 10 rebounds for his 30th double-double of
the season, and blocked seven shots as the Spurs ended the 11-game
winning streak of the league-leading Jazz.
</P>
<P>
One night after becoming the third team to clinch a playoff
berth, the Spurs climbed within three games of the Jazz, who had
knocked San Antonio out of the playoffs in three of the last five
years.
</P>
<P>
Karl Malone had 23 points and 13 rebounds to lead the Jazz as
it saw its longest winning streak in the NBA this season halted.
</P>
<P>
At Golden State, Kobe Bryant scored 27 points as the Los
Angeles Lakers rallied from a 28-point second-quarter deficit
without Shaquille O'Neal to beat the Warriors 106-102 in overtime.
</P>
<P>
O'Neal was ejected in the second quarter and the Lakers trailed
by 16 at the half. But Bryant scored 25 points after intermission,
including a tying tip-in at the regulation buzzer and a key dunk
in overtime.
</P>
<P>
In Toronto, Chris Crawford scored a career-high 18 points and
Mookie Blaylock added 16 to lead six Hawks in double figures as
Atlanta posted a 103-81 victory over the Raptors.
</P>
<P>
This was the first time for the Hawks to reach triple figures,
while Toronto (20-21) fell one game behind Cleveland in the race
for the final playoff berth in the Eastern Conference.
</P>
<P>
In Chicago, Toni Kukoc had 25 points, seven rebounds and nine
assists before leaving in the fourth quarter with a shoulder
injury as the Bulls posted an 83-77 victory over the Washington
Wizards.
</P>
<P>
In Dallas, Michael Finley burned his former team with a season-
high 36 points, including a jumper and two free throws in the
final 6.5 seconds, as the Mavericks downed the Phoenix Suns 104-
100.
</P>
<P>
In Milwaukee, Glenn Robinson scored 18 points as the Bucks
rallied for a 95-83 victory over the Orlando Magic and held the
sixth place in the East, one game ahead of Philadelphia. 
</P>
