<HEADLINE> Chinese Stone Exports Up 11.2 Percent Last Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua)-- China earned over 700 million U.S.
dollars by exporting 4.86 million tons of stone materials last
year, according to a recent report in the China Economic Times.
</P>
<P>
This figure was 11.2 percent higher than in 1997. China also
imported 1.01 million tons of stones last year, up 13.55 percent
over 1997.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted experts as saying that the world demand for
stone materials will reach 50 million tons by 2010, 68 percent
more than the current level. China is now the world's second-
largest stone-material producer.
</P>
<P>
The experts spoke at a recent international stone and equipment
show in Beijing, where stone tablets, carving, and related
materials were on display. 
</P>
