Masashi Motoyama, who was currently in Negeria with Japan's Under
20 side at the World Youth Championship, as he scored a hat trick
in Kashima Antlers' demolition of Malaysian side Sarawak in the
quarter-finals of the Asian Cup Winners Cup, the AFC said.
