<HEADLINE> Xinhua Economic News Summary at 05:00 GMT April 21 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANIERO -- Brazil's chicken exports rose in volume and
value in the first quarter of the year, in comparison with the
same period of 1998.
</P>
<P>
External sales over the period from January to March reached 154,
722 tons with a value of 188.2 million U.S. dollars, said Claudio
Martins, director of the Brazilian Association of Chicken
Exporters (BACE), according to a local newspaper on Tuesday.(
Brazil-Chicken)
</P>
<P>
- - - - - -
</P>
<P>
MEXICO CITY -- The rebound in Mexico's oil prices, which gained
up to five U.S.dollars in the last four months, will have a
favorable impact on Mexican economy, said the financial group BBV-
Probursa on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Adolfo Albo, director of economic studies of the financial
group, attributed the improvement of the Mexican economy to the
rebound in crude prices, the solidity of the U.S. economy and a
relief in the Brazilian crisis.
</P>
<P>
According to local press, the price of the Mexican oil exports
Monday passed the 14-dollar barrier per barrel, reaching the
highest for the last 15 months.(Mexico-Oil)
</P>
<P>
- - - - -
</P>
<P>
PANAMA CITY -- The Banana Exporting Countries Union (BECU) is
looking for new markets in China and the Middle East, a high
official of the organization said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Tax restrictions imposed by the European Union on the Central
American countries forced BECU members to turn to the gigantic
Asian market, Beatriz Garcia, coordinator of the Inter American
Agriculture Institute with the Banana Union, said.
</P>
<P>
Describing China as a very successful market, he added, "If
each of the 1.2 billion Chinese citizens ate just one banana
produced by the BECU countries, the problem of the search for new
markets would be resolved." (BECU-Banana-Market)
</P>
<P>
- - - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. President Bill Clinton on Tuesday urged the
international community to take steps to strengthen the global
financial system in a bid to prevent financial crises from
reaching catastrophic stages in the future.
</P>
<P>
After meeting with his top economic advisers, Clinton said the
United States would work with finance ministers from the world's
major economies, meeting in Washington this weekend, to build
support for his financial proposals before a June summit in
Germany of leaders of the major industrial economies.(Clinton-
Global Economy)
</P>
<P>
- - - - -
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- Japan's merchandise trade surplus increased to 14,096.
9 billion yen (about 118.8 billion dollars) in the fiscal year of
1998, up 23.1 percent from the previous year, the Finance Ministry
said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The ministry attributed the rise, which has gained for two
fiscal years in a row, to a plunge in imports.
</P>
<P>
Japan's exports dropped 3.8 percent to 49,450.7 billion yen (
about 416.6 billion dollars) in the fiscal of 1998, while imports
totaled 35,353.8 billion yen (about 297.8 billion dollars), both
marking the first decline in five fiscal years, the ministry said.
(Japan-Trade-Surplus) 
</P>
