<HEADLINE> Peru's Fishery Production Rebounds in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Peru's fishery production in the
first quarter of this year rose by 480 percent to 388,700 tons as
against 67,000 in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, fish exports increased by 140 percent, registering a
total of 313,000 tons, according to the Fishing Ministry Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Peru, one of the major fishery producers and exporters suffered
great damage last year due to the El Nino phenomenon.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the National Fishing Society (NFS) estimated that
this year the total volume of catch will come close to six million
tons, making 800 million dollars for the nation.
</P>
<P>
Fishery production will hit eight million tons as of the year
2000, which will permit the export revenue to reach some 1.2
million dollars. 
</P>
