<HEADLINE> Survey of Job Seekers' Preferences </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Computer-related jobs have become
the No 1 choice among young Chinese under 25, when they rate the
occupation they would prefer, according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
Preferences do not seem to be determined by salary, promotion
opportunities and social status, according to a survey conducted
by the Beijing-based Sunsway Information Company, which analyzed
questionnaires collected from 1,542 job seeks.
</P>
<P>
The average age of those who want to do clerical work, computer-
related jobs and advertising work is below 25.
</P>
<P>
Computer science, a fast changing industry with great
development potential and high income, is especially suitable for
young Chinese who are quick to accept new ideas, according to the
survey.
</P>
<P>
Secretarial work does not require high academic achievement or
deep experience. However, it asks for adaptability and insight,
qualities found in young people.
</P>
<P>
The advertising industry, which also demands insights and
activity, is appreciated by those who enjoy challenges.
</P>
<P>
More mature people favors jobs with professional skills and
experience. Those people who seek jobs in the finance sector,
management, real estate and law firms are mostly above 27 years
old.
</P>
<P>
The survey shows that most people engaged in business
management and the real estate industry are over 30.
</P>
<P>
When people gain more experience, they tend to choose jobs that
require high degrees of professionalism. They appreciate not only
challenges but also stability, according to the survey.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
