<HEADLINE> State of Emergency Declared for Two Argentine Provinces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, April 20 (Xinhua) -- A state of emergency has
been declared for Chaco and Formosa provinces of Argentina due to
heavy rains.
</P>
<P>
Torrential rains flooded Chaco's countryside, leaving rural
productive sectors in a critical state.
</P>
<P>
In Formosa province, grave inundation has effected 55
communities, making about 6,000 people flee their homeland.
</P>
<P>
Bank collapses of the Pilcomauo and Bermejo rivers have
affected thousands of residents in the two provinces and blocked
29 highways and local roads, with 36 schools isolated. 
</P>
