<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangxi Stages Rhesus Monkey Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- A rhesus monkey festival opened
recently in a nature reserve in southwest China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region, where tourists can enjoy the pleasure of
playing with these wild creature.
</P>
<P>
The Longhu Mountain Nature Reserve's 1,000 hectares is almost
completely covered with forest, preserving 215 varieties of wild
animals and over 1,200 plant species. The reserve is also home to
2,500 rhesus monkeys, making it China's largest breeding center
for the animal.
</P>
<P>
The reserve was opened to tourists in 1980, and the staff has
tamed many of the monkeys to play leisurely with the visitors who
they hope will develop a sense of wildlife protection.
</P>
<P>
The festival, the first of its kind in Guangxi, was scheduled
for the breeding season of the rhesus monkey, when tourists can
have the pleasure of watching the sporting of the animal.
</P>
<P>
A variety of other tourist activities such as the antiphonal
singing of the Zhuang ethnic minority people are presented at the
festival, which has been designated by the local government as an
important promotional event for Guangxi's abundant tourist
resources.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
