<HEADLINE> International Kite Festival Opens in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Some 70 kite-flying teams from
France, Japan, the United States and 24 other countries and
regions have come to Weifang, a major city in east China's
Shandong Province, to attend the ongoing 16th Weifang
International Kite Festival.
</P>
<P>
More than 40,000 spectators from both at home and abroad
attended the opening ceremony held yesterday evening.
</P>
<P>
During the following two days, the festival, the largest of its
kind in China, will present events including an international kite-
flying competition, a kite-flying exhibition, and a dragon boat
race.
</P>
<P>
The city is also presenting several trade fairs open to both
domestic and overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
An official from the city government said that since it began
in 1984, the annual kite festival has attracted over two million
people from dozens of countries and regions who come to exhibit
their kite-flying skills and watch a spectacular show.
</P>
<P>
The city of Weifang has established economic and trade ties
with over 50 countries and regions, and has approved about 2,400
overseas-funded enterprises, with total contractual overseas
capital of 3.41 billion U.S. dollars.  
</P>
