<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 21 (Xinhua) -- NATO jets early Wednesday bombed
the Belgrade headquarters of Yugoslav President Slobodan
Milosevic's ruling Socialist Party (SPS) and left the high-rise
building in flames.
</P>
<P>
Belgrade's civil defense chief Gragan Covic told a local
television station after the attack that the raid "certainly
caused casualties."
</P>
<P>
Several missiles hit the building, known as the Business
Center Usce, at 03:15 a.m. local time. The building is located in
the heart of Novi Belgrade, just opposite the Hyatt hotel where
many foreign reporters stay.
</P>
<P>
The top floor and the first three floors of the 25-storey
building were on fire when fire engines and other emergency
vehicles arrived at site.
</P>
<P>
Police have blocked access to the building, which also houses
several private radio and television stations, including Kosava,
which belongs to Milosevic's daughter Marija, and the popular
channel Pink. 
