<HEADLINE> Lithuanians to Face Italians in Euro League Basketball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Zalgiris Kaunas of Lithuania upset
Greeks Olympiakos 87-71 on Tuesday to join holders Kinder Bologna
of Italy in the EuroLeague basketball final.
</P>
<P>
It was the first appearance for Kaunas in a Final Four
tournament who will meet the Italians after the holders beat city
rivals Teamsystem 62-57 in another semifinal.
</P>
<P>
Olympiakos, winners in 1997, could do little to counter the
Lithuanian champions who were anchored by former NBA player
Anthony Bowie with accurate shots and Czech center Jiri Zidek with
numerous rebounds.
</P>
<P>
Kaunas, which nurses Arvydas Sabonis for the Portland Trail
Blazers in NBA, led from start to finish and were 48-33 ahead at
halftime, stayed firmly in the second half as Bowie scored the
most of 19 points.
</P>
<P>
"We've had great games but this was really our best game of the
year," Bowie said.
</P>
<P>
In the other semifinal, Kinder started perfectly to lead 20-9
after 11 minutes before Teamsystem, in a Final Four for the first
time, fought back to 32-34 at halftime through gunfires from
Carlton Myers, top scorer with 18 points.
</P>
<P>
Two points and a free throw from guard Marko Jaric put
Teamsystem to move ahead for the first time with a 35-34 lead one
minute into the second half, but Kinder, helped by centre Radoslav
Nesterovic, were soon back in command. 
</P>
