<HEADLINE> 36 kg of Cocaine Seized in Brazilian Military Aircraft </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Thirty-six kilograms of cocaine
was seized from a Brazilian military aircraft on Monday, the
Federal Police said.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time a Brazilian military aircraft was found
involved in drug-trafficking.
</P>
<P>
The confiscated cocaine, contained in 32 packets inside two
suitcases, was almost 100 percent pure and has a value of 3
million U.S.dollars, according to specialists.
</P>
<P>
The nine passengers of the Hercules C-130 plane of the
Brazilian Air Force, including one official, were detained Monday
evening at the base in Recife, capital of Pernambuco State in the
northeast of the country.
</P>
<P>
The Air Force aircraft was destined to Palma de Mallorca in
Spain from Rio de Janeiro.
</P>
<P>
The detained passengers will be subject to investigations by
the Federal Police and the Air Force authority. 
</P>
</TEXT>
