<HEADLINE> 4 ASEAN Countries to Be Linked by Railway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- International monetary
institutions will finance the development of a railway system that
will link Indonesia, Malaysia, Brunei Darussalam and the
Philippines.
</P>
<P>
"The plan is a follow-up of the Brunei Darussalam, Indonesia,
Malaysia and the Philippines East Asian Growth Area (BIMP-EAGA)
meeting. It is to be known as the Trans Borneo and Mindanao
Railway System," head of the South Kalimantan development planning
body Ismet Achmad said in the provincial capital of Banjarmasin on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The four countries are members of the Association of Southeast
Asian Nations (ASEAN).
</P>
<P>
The funds will come from the Asian Development Bank, the World
Bank and Germany which has conducted research on the railway
system.
</P>
<P>
"The planned construction of the railway system which will be
integrated with the other transportation lines, including the
ferry system to the Philippine Mindanao, will commence by 2001 and
is expected to be completed by 2005," Achmad was quoted by The
Indonesian Observer Wednesday as saying.
</P>
<P>
He expressed a hope that the system would make for all economic
potential to be explored. 
</P>
</TEXT>
