<HEADLINE> Russia Will Only Be Mediator in Yugoslavia Crisis: Chernomyrdin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin's
envoy Viktor Chernomyrdin said Tuesday that Russia will only act
as an mediator in solving the ongoing Yugoslavia crisis.
</P>
<P>
The current Balkan conflict has great bearing not only on
Russia but also the entire world since it is a dangerous precedent
to all countries, Chernomyrdin was quoted by Itar-Tass as telling
Azeri President Geidar Aliyev in the Azeri capital of Baku.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslavia crisis has already entered a "dead-end" and
NATO's intensive bombardment could only worsen the situation
rather than provide a settlement, he said.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin said NATO's destructive military attacks in the
region must be halted and safe returns of Kosovo refugees be
facilitated.
</P>
<P>
He also urged the international community to work together for
a peaceful solution to the conflict.
</P>
<P>
After his stay in Azerbaijan, Chernomyrdin, Yeltsin's envoy to
seek a peaceful settlement for the Balkan crisis, will travel to
Ukraine to continue his three-nation tour which has already taken
him to Georgia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
