<HEADLINE> Oil Prices Rebound to Help Mexican Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The rebound in Mexico's oil
prices, which gained up to five U.S.dollars in the last four
months, will have a favorable impact on Mexican economy, said the
financial group BBV-Probursa on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Adolfo Albo, director of economic studies of the financial
group, attributed the improvement of the Mexican economy to the
rebound in crude prices, the solidity of the U.S. economy and a
relief in the Brazilian crisis.
</P>
<P>
According to local press, the price of the Mexican oil exports
Monday passed the 14-dollar barrier per barrel, reaching the
highest for the last 15 months.
</P>
<P>
"Over the last three months," said Albo, "the financial markets
had an extraordinary performance" helped by a solid base.
</P>
<P>
Albo said that the rebound in prices in the international
market may do help to a political strengthening of the country,
with the nearing of the presidential elections of the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
He added that lower inflationary rates are also a favorable
factor. "We are seeing better rates", he said, adding this helped
national economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
