<HEADLINE> Bugalski Leads Catalonia Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Philippe Bugalski of France took
the overall lead in the Catalonia Rally on Tuesday, finishing the
second day stages with a 17.7-second margin over countryman Didier
Auriol.
</P>
<P>
Bugalski of Citroen Xsara, who started in third place, clocked
an overall time of 3 hours 14 minutes 33.1 seconds while Spain's
Jesus Puras, the first-day leader, withdrew due to mechanical
problems.
</P>
<P>
World champion Tommi Makinen of Finland, who drives for
Mitsubishi, is fifth with 2:09.2 behind Bugalski.
</P>
<P>
The rally, which finishes Wednesday, is the fifth event of the
World Rally season and the first to be held on pure tarmac.
</P>
<P>
Spain's Carlos Sainz, Auriol's Toyota teammate, is third after
overcoming a flat tire in the fifth of the six time-trial stages.
</P>
<P>
However, Makinen still leads the world standings with
Scotland's Collin McRae just two points back as the Ford driver
withdrew at the end of the second day.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, McRae dropped from 19th to 21st because of a tire
problem in the last stage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
