<HEADLINE> Hainan to Accelerate Poverty Relief Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, April 21 (Xinhua) -- South China's Hainan Province
plans to help 35,000 disabled people escape poverty this year.
</P>
<P>
Wu Qun, chairman of the Hainan Disabled Persons Federation,
said that the province will accelerate poverty relief efforts in
1999 and will achieve its goal of eliminating absolute poverty by
the end of this century.
</P>
<P>
Disabled individuals in 19 Hainan cities and counties will
receive relief funds or loans totaling five million yuan (602,400
US dollars) in 1999, said Wu, adding that disabled families will
receive an average of between 1,000-3,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The federation has granted poverty relief loans of some 100
million yuan over the past three years, with related funds
enabling 18,000 disabled people to open private businesses and
providing basic supports for 26,876 disabled people.  
</P>
