<HEADLINE> China Strengthens Steel Quality to Ensure Construction Projects Safety </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- China is taking stringent
measures to prevent low-quality steel products from entering the
market as a bid to guarantee the safety of construction projects,
said today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The State Bureau of Quality and Technical Supervision and the
State Administration of Metallurgical Industry have jointly issued
a regulation, which requires all steel products for construction
use to conform to the set quality standards.
</P>
<P>
The regulation demands that all producers, sales agencies and
involved units follow the regulation strictly. Violation of the
regulation will incur severe punishment including withdrawal of
sales licenses and possible law suits.
</P>
<P>
The regulation stipulates that steel manufacturers must acquire
production licenses issued by the metallurgical bureau. In
addition, all products have to be carefully examined before
leaving the factory and have a quality certificate.
</P>
<P>
Factories without the required technology, equipment and
examination facilities will not be granted a license, said the
regulation.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted government officials as saying that steel used
in dams and state-level key projects must be re-inspected by a
third party.
</P>
<P>
There have been in recent years an apparent increase of
accidents involving inferior construction, which has called for
government attention. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
