<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Foreign Exchange Reserves Decline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Bank Indonesia's net foreign
exchange reserves declined to 15.86 billion U.S. dollars on April
15 from 15.93 billion dollars on April 7, the Jakarta Post
Wednesday quoted the central bank's weekly report as saying.
</P>
<P>
The central bank said repayment of foreign loans contributed to
the slight fall in net foreign exchange reserves.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, the report said, the level was still above the
International Monetary Fund (IMF) adjusted net international
reserves of 11.3 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Gross international reserves, which are net foreign exchange
reserves plus outstanding foreign exchange contracts, also
declined to 25.84 billion dollars on April 15 from 25.93 billion
dollars on April 7, the bank said. 
</P>
