<HEADLINE> Parma Book UEFA Cup Final Berth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Parma defeated Atletico Madrid 2-1
on Tuesday for a 5-2 aggregate triumph, securing their place in
the UEFA Cup final against Olympique Marseille in Moscow next
month.
</P>
<P>
As goalkeeper Gianluigi Buffon dived for several fine saves,
Abel Balbo scored the opener in the first half and Enrico Chiesa
netted in the winner for the Italians who established a 3-1 lead
from the first leg in Spain two weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
The Spaniards tried hard for an early strike, but all their
efforts were blocked by Buffon who saved David Tevenet's header
and two long-range shots by Oscar Mena.
</P>
<P>
And it was Parma who eventually fired home first when Juan
Veron sliced through Atletico's midfield, rushed along the left
and slid a perfect pass for Balbo who scored with an angled shot
on the run.
</P>
<P>
After the interval, Roberto rose at the near post to head a 64
th-minute corner from Oscar Mena past Buffon.
</P>
<P>
Parma, winners of the UEFA Cup in 1995, regained their lead
with eight minutes to go when Chiesa connected a pass 15 meters
from Balbo and slammed home with his left foot. 
</P>
</TEXT>
