<HEADLINE> Penalty Kick Puts Olympique Marseille in UEFA Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 20 (Xinhua) -- With four minutes to go, captain
Laurent Blanc scored a penalty against Bologna on Tuesday, taking
Olympique Marseille into the UEFA Cup final against Parma in
Moscow on May 12.
</P>
<P>
The penalty kick, which resulted in a brawl on and off the
pitch, prevented an otherwise all-Italian UEFA final as Bologna,
who drew 0-0 in Marseille, were leading 1-0 after 86 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Bologna goalkeeper Francesco Antonioli pulled down striker
Florian Maurice in the box just as the Italians seemed destined to
reach the first European final in their 90-year-history.
</P>
<P>
Blanc was forced to take his spot kick twice and his second
shot took the 1993 European champions through to their first UEFA
Cup final on away goals.
</P>
<P>
Two minutes later, Bologna had its Giancarlo Marocchi fired for
a crude challenge on striker Aboubacar Camara.
</P>
<P>
After the final whistle, riots erupted as a Bologna player
punched Blanc on his way to the dressing room, which lasted for
minutes before riot police intervened. 
</P>
