<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Publishes First Military History Photo Album </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- China recently published its
first photo album covering the country's 7,000-year military
history.
</P>
<P>
The album, published by the Hunan People's Publishing House and
Hunan Education Press, features photographs ranging from stone
weapons used by primitive societies to advanced fighter aircraft,
as well as photos of famous Chinese military strategists.
</P>
<P>
Editor in Chief Yuan Wei said the 4,000-odd photos in the album
provide a relatively complete survey of Chinese military history,
including famous battles, military theories, systems and primary
weapons.
</P>
<P>
Gai Shengfu, deputy curator at the Military Museum of the
Chinese People's Revolution, noted that China has a long military
history rarely found in other countries.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the album contains some photos and documents
published for the first time.
</P>
<P>
Experts point out that the photo album will be highly valuable
for continuing historical and academic research.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
