<HEADLINE> (updates with more details) At Least 20 hurt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 20 (Xinhua) -- At least 20 people were
wounded as two young men in black trench coats and masks opened
fire Tuesday at a high school southwest of Denver, capital of the
Colorado State of the United States.
</P>
<P>
Three men in black have been detained so far, and unconfirmed
reports said the men are friends of the suspects.
</P>
<P>
The injured were taken to the nearby hospitals. Local
television reported that one female student got nine gunshots in
the chest.
</P>
<P>
Explosions also were heard inside the Columbine High School.
Witnesses said the gunmen tossed an explosive device.
</P>
<P>
The shootings took place at the lunch time around the school,
including the cafeteria and library. The Columbine High School
has an enrollment of 1800 students.
</P>
<P>
"They were just shooting. They don't care who they shot,"
said one eyewitness.
</P>
<P>
About 100 to 200 law enforcement officers rushed to the scene
and the area was cordoned off.
</P>
<P>
All the nearby schools were also closed for the safety of the
students.
</P>
<P>
A series of school shootings since 1997 shocked the nation and
led to calls for tighter security and closer monitoring of troubled
students.
</P>
<P>
Two were killed at a school in Pearl, Mississipi, three at West
Paducah, Kansas, five at Jonesboro, Arkansas, and two at a school in
Springfield, Oregon.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics released by U.S. Department of Education
last year, attacks with weapons accounted for almost 11,000
incidents in public schools during the 1996-97 school year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
