<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Move Higher After Setback </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
NEW YORK, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The Wall Street stocks
recovered Tuesday from a previous setback.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average finished up 8.02 at
10,448.55 in struggling to push higher despite profit-taking.
The index stepped into the positive territory a few
minutes before the closing of trading.
</P>
<P>
The Dow lost 53.36 points Monday as traders sold blue
chips to lock in the gains made in the record high trading
last week.
</P>
<P>
The technology heavy Nasdaq index made an aggressive
comeback after losing 138.43 points in the previous session.
The composite index closed up 64.03 to 2,409.64.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index rose 16.69 at 1,306.17 and
the NYSE composite index rose 4.96 at 620.84.
</P>
<P>
The American Stock Exchange index rose 1.87 at 736.98 while
the Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose 2.93 at 415.34.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 6-to-5 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,396 up, 1,680 down and 489
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume declined to 975.88 million shares from 1.2
billion in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
